Just a thought. First off. Great opportunity taking advantage of a wrecked truck and taking the time to fix it. Thats a way to save some dough depending on how much was spent to recover it. I am sure you guys have enough wealth of knowledge to get it back up and running in excellent condition. But here is a thought. To the poor guy or gal that was driving it, how cool would it be to get this tank back on the road and back to the owner? Of course im sure the owner had gap insurance and is probably seeking to buy a new set of wheels but what a compliment it would be to bring it back so he can bounce back on the road for the holidays?

But like I said i dont know the circumstance but of I had the money and the heart, thats what id do. Either way enjoy the rebuild project and congrats on the new tow rig haha

snippet.textDisplay:
This comment has nothing to do with my opinion of the goonzquad. Anymore, with YT posters with more than 100,000 subs, anyone who (Dares) make a comment that even "appears" to be negative (even if it's not) and suddenly everyone becomes a keyboard "warrior" and attacks you for expressing an actual opinion that might not be the same as every other Lemming in the comments section. So, now that that if out of the way.
For those of you who get easily bored or easily distracted, I recommend changing the video speed level to x1.5 or even x2. This makes the video take less of your time, thereby giving you more time to watch more videos. It helps to stay focused on the task at hand, but most importantly it makes the video about 5 times more entertaining! If you thought the boys were motivated and energetic Before, you should see them on a higher speed. It's legit like they are on crack, lmao! 😂 It really makes everything better. I noticed that there are some people who have a negative opinion on the music, and those people usually get away with complaining about it without any backlash, well for those of you, I've noticed that even when the music is not exactly flowing according to My taste having it at a higher speed makes it sound completely different, and IMO, better. Finally tbh, I am no longer able to watch videos (on Any channel) at regular speed. It's like I'm watching in slow motion, and the voices don't even seem to line up with the audio. I'm perfectly fine with this, because like I said, it doesn't take as long to get thru videos, therefore you can watch more videos, and it makes Every video more lively and entertaining. The Only exceptions to this would be if I'm watching some kind of performance, like singing, dancing, or some kind of event like sports or something similar. Also, if I am watching at higher speeds and I happen to miss something, then all I have to do is rewind the video. This is rare, and I like to run with subtitles on a lot of the time anyways, so it's very rare that I miss something altogether.
In the end, I will end up getting to enjoy as much as twice as many videos as the typical YT user which to me is Fantastic!!✌️✌️
snippet.textOriginal:
This comment has nothing to do with my opinion of the goonzquad. Anymore, with YT posters with more than 100,000 subs, anyone who (Dares) make a comment that even "appears" to be negative (even if it's not) and suddenly everyone becomes a keyboard "warrior" and attacks you for expressing an actual opinion that might not be the same as every other Lemming in the comments section. So, now that that if out of the way. 
For those of you who get easily bored or easily distracted, I recommend changing the video speed level to x1.5 or even x2. This makes the video take less of your time, thereby giving you more time to watch more videos. It helps to stay focused on the task at hand, but most importantly it makes the video about 5 times more entertaining! If you thought the boys were motivated and energetic Before, you should see them on a higher speed. It's legit like they are on crack, lmao! 😂 It really makes everything better. I noticed that there are some people who have a negative opinion on the music, and those people usually get away with complaining about it without any backlash, well for those of you, I've noticed that even when the music is not exactly flowing according to My taste having it at a higher speed makes it sound completely different, and IMO, better. Finally tbh, I am no longer able to watch videos (on Any channel) at regular speed. It's like I'm watching in slow motion, and the voices don't even seem to line up with the audio. I'm perfectly fine with this, because like I said, it doesn't take as long to get thru videos, therefore you can watch more videos, and it makes Every video more lively and entertaining. The Only exceptions to this would be if I'm watching some kind of performance, like singing, dancing, or some kind of event like sports or something similar. Also, if I am watching at higher speeds and I happen to miss something, then all I have to do is rewind the video. This is rare, and I like to run with subtitles on a lot of the time anyways, so it's very rare that I miss something altogether. 
In the end, I will end up getting to enjoy as much as twice as many videos as the typical YT user which to me is Fantastic!!✌️✌️
